    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Death Row: No Room for Error</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Carl Silverman letter says even small chance that an innocent person might be executed is enough reason to oppose death penalty (July 10 Op-Ed article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>James Q. Wilson (Op-Ed, July 10) blandly asserts that opponents of the death penalty should not base their arguments on the ''tiny chance that someday somebody innocent will be killed.'' Why not? Sounds like a pretty good reason to me.</p>
        <p>CARL SILVERMAN  Madison, Wis., July 10, 2000</p>
      </block>
